Ok, than i hear it like you do. Isn't the idea of posting=
 files to get different theories on what is heard? What are we comprehendin=
g in these or any other files anyway? We are just starting to break ground =
on full sentence answers, so we need to sift through them and make sense. T=
hat one about the earthquake is a great file, but what does it mean??? It d=
oesn't make any sense, we have to make sense of these files. Whether it be =
in reverse, enhancing the audio or whatever. This is our job as researchers=
, while they laugh their ass off on the other side watching us spend hours =
on the computer to say there is going to be an earthquake somewhere that do=
esn't happen. If they say 'Steve likes cupcakes in a tree in east asia', th=
at's a great file and it will be clear. But what would it mean and what eff=
ect will it have on humanity.Nuff Said'-Steve H.--- In EVP-ITC@yahoogroups.=
